# Skill #3 - Brackets Setup

Skill Demonstration Challenge

---

## Objective

Demonstrate that Brackets is properly configured for development

* Brackets is pinned to Start Bar
* Open Folder is set up
* Beatify extension is active


## Steps

### Pin Brackets
* Click on Start Menu and type "Brackets"
* Pin Brackets to Windows Start Menu Bar
    * Right-click on Brackets Icon
    * Choose Pin


### Open Folder
* The "Open Folder" feature is powerful so use it
* One the right side-panel select Open Folder
* Browse to your BACS 200 code
* Remove the "Getting Started" menu item by clicking on the "x"

    
### Setup Brackets with Beautify
* Install Beatify Extension
    * File menu, Extension Manager
    * Search for Beatify
    * Install button


### Using Beautify
* Edit menu, Beatify
* Enable on Save for automatic indents


### Create New File
* Paste in this funky code and use Beautify to fix indenting

```
    <!DOCTYPE html>
        <html lang="en">
        <head>
        <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Basic Page Template</title>
        </head>
        <body>
    <h1>Basic Page Template</h1>
        <p>This is a very simple page to show how to create an HTML file.</p>
    <p>To see the HTML Code select menu item "Tools, Web Developer, Page Source" or "Ctrl-U".</p>
            </body>
                    </html>
```



